tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE user_wishlist (
    user_id INT,
    item_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES wishlist_users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (item_id) REFERENCES wishlist_items(item_id),
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, item_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(255),
    email VARCHAR(255),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE wishlists (
    wishlist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT REFERENCES users(user_id),
    wishlist_name VARCHAR(255),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE items (
    item_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    wishlist_id INT REFERENCES wishlists(wishlist_id),
    item_name VARCHAR(255),
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
)

CREATE TABLE categories (
    category_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    category_name VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE users (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE wishlists (
  wishlist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  wishlist_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT current_timestamp
)

CREATE TABLE items (
  item_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  item_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  item_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE wishlist_items (
  wishlist_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  wishlist_id INT,
  item_id INT,
  quantity INT DEFAULT 1
)

CREATE TABLE categories (
  category_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  category_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
)
